<h1><a name="begin_content"></a>Audit (A-04-08-00047)</h1>

<h2>11-25-2009<br />
Review of Georgia’s Pandemic Influenza Expenditures for the Period August 31, 2005, Through June 30, 2008</h2>

<h2 class="line">Executive Summary</h2>


<p>As of June 30, 2008, Georgia’s Division of Public Health, Office of Preparedness (the State agency) had spent $4.9 million of the $14 million in pandemic influenza (pan flu) funding that it received from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.  The unspent funds totaled $9 million, or 65 percent of the cumulative awarded amount.</p>

<p>We reviewed $2.9 million of the $4.9 million charged to the award and concluded that $2.5 million complied with Federal cost requirements.  The remaining $379,000 was not allowable.  Specifically, $255,000 was not adequately documented, and $125,000 did not meet Federal cost requirements. </p> 


